The cost of company's debt refers to the effective rate at which the company pays their debt. This can be solved by first taking the yield to maturity of each of the bonds presented. The yield to maturity can be solved using this formula:

$$\begin{aligned}
\text{Yield to maturity}&=\dfrac{\text{Coupon payment}+\frac{\text{Face value}-\text{Present value}}{\text{Years to maturity}}}{\frac{\text{Face value}+\text{Present value}}{2}}
\end{aligned}$$

In the case of all computations here, we will make use of face value equal to $1000$.
